RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 68. Maiden Special Weight Purse 31000. FOR MN-BRED MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ARTIE BELOW ZERO chased the leader between horses up the backstretch, challenged from the two path coming around the turn and dueled to the wire, edging clear late. R VOO'S TABOO led the way up the backstretch, dueled while saving ground around the bend and dug in in the lane but was outfinished late. SWEET ANALYZER raced in the middle of the pack on the outside through the opening quarter of a mile, navigated the turn from the two path and finished evenly, no match for the top two. ANGEL OF ATTACK bumped with the horse to his outside leaving the gate, trailed the field early, saved ground around the turn and improved position mildly in the stretch while never truly threatening. B L'S CONCERTO veered out leaving the gate, recovered to stalk the leader on the outside up the backstretch, came around the bend in the three path and faded from there. PRESTIGIOUSLY WILD bumped with the horse to his outside leaving the gate, settled off the pace for the run up the backstretch, continued around the turn in the three path and was empty in the stretch.

ENTRY.NAME: Artie Below Zero
ENTRY.OWNER: Aguilera Thomas V and Aguilera Janet

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 2 7 1/2F Turf CR: 45. Maiden Claiming Purse 10500. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000. Minnesota Bred Claiming Price $15,000. (If management deems it inadvisable to run this race on the turf, two-year-old races will be run at 6 and 1/2 furlongs and races for three-year-olds and up will be run at a distance of 1 mile on the main track.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MISS CARMEN CIBO veered in and bumped with the horse too her inside leaving the gate, raced in the two path early, led the way up the backstretch, saved ground around the bend and held clear while drifting some in the final furlong. LIKE FINE WINE chased the leader on the outside through the opening half mile, navigated the far bend from the three path and kept on to the wire. DELUSIONAL DREAM hopped up leaving the gate, raced in the two path around the first bend, continued up the backstretch off the pace, began a bid from the three path coming around the second turn and chased on to the finish. MIZZEN GEE MA was bumped by the horse to her outside at the start, saved ground early, settled in the middle of the pack on the inside for the run up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the far turn and finished evenly. MARK OF VICTORY raced in the middle of the pack between horses around the first turn and up the backstretch, saved ground around the far bend and flattened out in the stretch. MIZ MCCOY raced in the three path around the first turn, settled in the middle of the pack on the outside for the run up the backstretch, continued around the far turn still in the three path and faded from there.

ENTRY.OWNER: Rosin Coty W Rosin Tim W and Kane Mark E

ENTRY.NAME: Miss Carmen Cibo
ENTRY.OWNER: Bravo Lori L and Schenian Dale

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 3 5F Turf CR: 81. Claiming Purse 14000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR MINNESOTA BRED WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000. Minnesota Bred Claiming Price $25,000. (If management deems it inadvisable to run this race on the Turf, it will be run at a distance of 5 Furlongs on the main track.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FUTURE PERFECT chased the leader up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn, began a bid nearing the quarter pole and quickly kicked clear. HI YAH led the field through the opening quarter, opened up while racing in the three path around the bend, was caught in upper stretch and chased the winner home from there. SUPREME CAPO raced in the middle of the pack early, saved ground around the turn and improved position in the lane. STAR OF STARS raced off the pace on the outside up the backstretch, continued around the turn in the three path and never threatened. STAR MISSION trailed the field up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn and showed no kick. LUCKY MCCOY raced off the pace on the inside early, continued around the turn in the two path and faded form there.

ENTRY.NAME: Hi Yah
ENTRY.OWNER: Bowen Tyler and Williams James T

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Frances Genter S. CANTERBURY PARK RACE 4 6F Dirt CR: 88. Stakes Purse 50000. FOR FILLIES, THREE YEARS OLD WHICH ARE REGISTERED MINNESOTA BREDS.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CUPIDS CRUSH pressed the pace on the outside up the backstretch, challenged from the two path coming around the turn and drew off in the stretch. CHECKCASHINGCONNIE chased the pace setters through the early going, navigated the turn from the three path and improved position in the lane while proving to be no match for the winner. ANN ALEE led the way on the inside up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn, was caught in upper stretch and weakened late. LOVER GIRL was blocked leaving the gate, raced off the pace on the outside up the backstretch, continued around the turn in the three path and was never a threat. MIGHTY MADI raced off the pace between horses through the opening quarter of a mile, came around the bend in the two path and made no bid. SPOILED BRAT raced at the back of the pack on the inside early, saved ground around the turn and was empty in the lane.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: XAVEY DAVE saved ground around the first turn, tracked the leader on the inside up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the far turn, began a bid from the rail entering the stretch, kicked clear and held off a closer at the wire. STAGECOACH BOYS chased the pace setter on the outside around the first turn and up the backstretch, began a bid from the two path coming around the far bend and gained ground late. THEALLIGATORHUNTER saved ground early, led the way up the backstretch, dueled while saving ground around the second turn, was caught in upper stretch and kept on to the finish.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 6 5F Turf CR: 88. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 28000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, TRIAL OR STATE BRED ALLOWANCE OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $16,000. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Si nce June 15 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000. Minnesota Bred Claiming Price $25,000. (If management deems it inadvisable to run this race on the Turf, it will be run at a distance of 5 Furlongs on the main track.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BAYOU COLONEL raced off the pace on the outside up the backstretch, came around the turn in the three path, launched a bid approaching the eighth pole, gained ground and pulled clear. RELEASED bumped with the horses to both sides leaving the gate, chased the pace setter up the backstretch, navigated the bend from the two path, switched inside to began a bid entering the stretch and gained ground late. MISTER BANJOMAN dueled on the outside through the opening quarter of a mile, continued to battle from the two path coming around the turn, dug in in upper stretch and was caught late. CHANNEL WON bumped with the horses to both sides at the start, raced off the pace between horses early, saved ground around the turn and gained ground late. DIVE DEEP tracked the pace setter on the outside up the backstretch, continued around the bend in the three path and was outkicked in the stretch. HAPPY HOUR BOBBY dueled on the inside up the backstretch, continued to battle while saving ground around the turn and weakened in the final furlong. SAMURAI MIKE bumped with the horse to his outside leaving the gate, raced off the pace through the opening stages, saved ground around the bend and made no bid. HURTS SO GOOD was pinched back leaving the gate, trailed the field up the backstretch, moved up while racing in the four path around the turn and flattened out in the lane.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Minnesota Turf Distaff S. CANTERBURY PARK RACE 7 7 1/2F Turf CR: 92. Stakes Purse 50000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH ARE REGISTERED MINNESOTA BREDS.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MIDNIGHT CURRENT saved ground around the first turn, chased the leader up the backstretch, came around the far turn in the two path, began a bid in upper stretch and dueled to the wire to just get the win. LET'S SKEDADDLE raced in the two path early, settled off the pace on the inside for the run up the backstretch, saved ground around the far turn, launched a bid between horses passing the three sixteenths pole and dueled to the finish from there to narrowly miss. SCENT OF SUCCESS tracked the leader on the outside through the opening half mile, challenged from the two path coming around the second bend and could not go with the top two in the stretch but kept on to the wire. SHE'S MY WARRIOR led the way while saving ground around the first turn and up the backstretch, dueled from the rail around the far turn, veered in at the eighth pole and weakened from there. MOLLY'S ANGEL raced in the three path early, trailed the field up the backstretch, moved up from the four path coming around the second bend and was outkicked in the lane. START SINGING raced in the three path around the first turn, settled off the pace on the outside for the run up the backstretch, continued around the far turn still in the three path and made no bid.

ENTRY.NAME: She's My Warrior
ENTRY.OWNER: Mattson Peter D and Padilla Tim P

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 8 1M Dirt CR: 69. Claiming Purse 12000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR MINNESOTA BRED WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000. Minnesota Bred Claiming Price $15,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DON'T BOX ME IN angled in to save ground racing around the first turn, led the way up the backstretch, came around the far bend in the two path and drew off in the lane, much the best. GRUNDER raced into traffic and steadied while saving ground around the first turn, settled off the pace on the inside for the run up the backstretch, continued around the second turn in the two path and gained ground late. BIG PETE tracked the pace setter on the outside through the opening half mile, continued around the far turn still in the three path and kept on to the wire. PASSTHECAT raced in the two path around the first bend, continued up the backstretch off the pace on the outside, navigated the far turn from the four path and passed tiring horses in the lane. TALE OF TRUTH raced in the two path early, chased the leader on the outside up the backstretch, came around the far turn still in the two path and faded in the stretch. THE SWAYZE EXPRESS raced in the middle of the pack in the three path around the first turn and up the backstretch, continued around the second turn in the three path and was empty from there. NACHO S raced in the three path around the first turn, trailed the field up the backstretch, saved ground around the far bend and was never a factor. UNIQUE PATH saved ground around the first turn, stalked the frontrunner on the inside up the backstretch, dropped back from the rail coming around the second turn and continued to tire in the lane. THE RIDER OF HORSE, GRUNDER, ONE CLAIMED FOUL AGAINST HORSE SEVEN, DONT BOX ME IN, CITING INTERFERENCE HEADED INTO THE FIRST TURN. UPON REVIEW, NO CHANGES WERE MADE TO THE ORDER OF FINISH.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Victor S. Myers S. CANTERBURY PARK RACE 9 6F Dirt CR: 88. Stakes Purse 50000. FOR COLTS AND GELDINGS, THREE YEARS OLD WHICH ARE REGISTERED MINNESOTA BREDS.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SIR STERLING brushed with the horse to his outside leaving the gate, recovered to lead the field on the inside up the backstretch, continued to show the way from the two path around the turn, kicked clear in the stretch and held that margin to the wire while drifting mildly late. ROSES BY LIAM tracked the leader on the inside through the opening quarter of a mile, saved ground around the bend and chased on to the finish. IT'S BOBS BUSINESS bumped with the horse to his inside at the start, raced off the pace early, began to move up coming around the turn, swung out to the five path coming into the stretch and improved position from there. DISTORTED PRO chased the leader between horses up the backstretch, navigated the bend from the three path and was outkicked in the stretch. WEST ISLAND tracked the pace setter between horses through the opening stages, came around the turn in the four path and weakened in the lane. CROCODILEHUNTER stalked the frontrunner on the outside up the backstretch, continued around the turn in the three path and tired in the lane.

ENTRY.NAME: Crocodilehunter
